<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hold a parade • make a parade</xh5><p> <i>hold a parade—</i>1. organize a procession of people or soldiers to celebrate a special day or event: The King is glad to know that the Boy Scouts are <u>holding their first annual parade</u>. 2. <i>(legal)</i> conduct a procedure in which the witness is asked to pick out the criminal from among a group of randomly selected people: Where there has been a failure to <u>hold a parade</u> the jury should be warned of the dangers of identification without a parade.</p><p><i>make a parade</i>—(of ) try to impress people by making a display of one’s abilities, virtues, etc.: They only want to <u>make a parade</u> of their wealth.</p> </entry>
